  "text": "Sociodemographic data. Using a general questionnaire, parental migrant status and educational level were determined, respectively, by the place of birth and the highest grade of school completed. [CITATION_1] According to their place of birth, we grouped migrant parents into the five following regions: Portugal, former Yugoslavia, rest of Europe (Germany, France, Spain, Italy, and Turkey), Africa, and rest of the world. Parents were defined as ''migrants'' if at least 1 of them was born outside of Switzerland [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] and as ''low educated'' if at least 1 of them had no education beyond obligatory school (9 years). Further questions included time spent by children with television viewing (min/d) and use of any medication.",
